### PHP PDO Basics

PDO (PHP Data Objects) provides a consistent interface for accessing multiple databases.

### PDO Connection

```php
<?php
$host = "localhost";
$db = "test_db";
$user = "root";
$pass = "";

try {
    $pdo = new PDO("mysql:host=$host;dbname=$db;charset=utf8mb4", $user, $pass);

    // Set error mode to exceptions
    $pdo->setAttribute(PDO::ATTR_ERRMODE, PDO::ERRMODE_EXCEPTION);

    // Set default fetch mode
    $pdo->setAttribute(PDO::ATTR_DEFAULT_FETCH_MODE, PDO::FETCH_ASSOC);

    echo "Connected successfully";
} catch (PDOException $e) {
    die("Connection failed: " . $e->getMessage());
}
?>
```

### PDO Query

```php
<?php
// Simple query (not for user input!)
$stmt = $pdo->query("SELECT * FROM users");
$users = $stmt->fetchAll();

foreach ($users as $user) {
    echo $user["name"] . "<br>";
}
?>
```

### Fetch Modes

| Mode | Returns |
|------|---------|
| `PDO::FETCH_ASSOC` | Associative array |
| `PDO::FETCH_NUM` | Numeric array |
| `PDO::FETCH_BOTH` | Both (default) |
| `PDO::FETCH_OBJ` | Object |
| `PDO::FETCH_CLASS` | Into a class |

### PDO Attributes

```php
<?php
$pdo->setAttribute(PDO::ATTR_ERRMODE, PDO::ERRMODE_EXCEPTION);
$pdo->setAttribute(PDO::ATTR_DEFAULT_FETCH_MODE, PDO::FETCH_ASSOC);
$pdo->setAttribute(PDO::ATTR_EMULATE_PREPARES, false);
?>
```

### Advantages of PDO

| Feature | PDO | mysqli |
|---------|-----|--------|
| Database support | 12+ databases | MySQL only |
| Named parameters | Yes | No |
| OOP interface | Yes | Both |
| Error handling | Exceptions | Mixed |
| Driver abstraction | Yes | No |

> **Key Point:** Always set `PDO::ERRMODE_EXCEPTION` for proper error handling and `PDO::ATTR_DEFAULT_FETCH_MODE` for consistent result format.
